{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"699ba47d-ad99-4590-b22f-e61dcddb11c6","content":"The template is **mostly valid** but has a few gaps before publishing:\n\n**✅ Good:**\n- `identity`, `name`, `shortName`, `author` — all required fields present\n- `sourceName` for namespace replacement\n- `classifications` and `tags` properly set\n- `symbols` with a valid choice parameter\n\n**❌ Issues to fix:**\n\n1. **Missing `$schema`** — Add for validation/IntelliSense:\n   ```json\n   \"$schema\": \"http://json.schemastore.org/template\"\n   ```\n\n2. **Missing `description`** — Required for NuGet discoverability. Without it, users see a blank description in `dotnet new search`.\n\n3. **`Framework` symbol isn't wired up** — The parameter exists but there's no `replaces` or `defaultValue` replacement connecting it to the `.csproj` `<TargetFramework>`. It won't actually change anything.\n\n**Recommendation:** Add `description`, the `$schema`, and wire the `Framework` symbol (e.g., via a `replaces` on `\"net9.0\"` in the project file) before publishing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f4aed615-101f-4fdb-9ff3-cc802606f66c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Let me review this template.json for NuGet publishing readiness. I'll check for required and recommended fields.\n\nRequired fields for a .NET template:\n- `$schema` - not present (recommended but not strictly required)\n- `identity` - ✅ present\n- `name` - ✅ present\n- `shortName` - ✅ present\n- `author` - ✅ present\n\nRecommended/important fields:\n- `$schema` - ❌ missing (helps with validation/intellisense)\n- `sourceName` - ✅ present\n- `classifications` - ✅ present\n\n\n- `tags` - ✅ present with language and type\n- `description` - ❌ missing (important for NuGet discoverability)\n- `groupIdentity` - ❌ missing (recommended for template packs)\n\nThe main gaps I'm seeing are the missing `$schema` for validation support, the absent `description` field which would hurt discoverability on NuGet, and I notice the `symbols.Framework` parameter has defined choices but I'm not certain it's actually wired up to control anything in the template generation.","outputTokens":646,"requestId":"7403:300A76:1BD2147:1EE14AA:69FA915C"},"id":"1cddb67d-bda3-467c-9de1-a112265fb019","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:55:08.142Z","parentId":"f66aeea3-5e80-4148-a123-8aacde51b634"}
